values:
So today....

1. I was lonely coz all my usual little friends had gone to Cardiff with St David's Choir or they were taking part in a netball tornement...

2. PSE made me want to shout 'WHY CAN'T WE BE LIBERAL AND HELPFUL LIKE THE NETHERLANDS??? WHYY!!!!!????' Since when has sex been a sin??? AND since when do teachers treat homosexuals as something 'we shouldn't talk about'???? FOR FUCKS SAKE!!!!!

3. We had to watch that shitty version of Romeo and Juliette with that little sod Leonardo Di Caprio. AGAIN! (Juliette is so easy...)

4. Tutor is nagging us for our options sheets back in...when we've only had them a week! WE'RE SUPPOST TO HAVE ALL THROUGH THE EASTER HOLS TO THINK ABOUT IT YOU STUPID PERSON!!!!!!!!

5. I'm getting bored of everything. I can't seem to keep my mind on the task. I'm drifting...

6. Ellen was trying to put my hair up my nose...


Wow, the guy on tv just said that this missile was guided by a GBS signal!!! Fo Shizz!

Anna is also taking over the band thing that I was part off. BIG SURPRISE! She's only in it coz somewhere in his head she thinks it'll get her closer to Gareth. Blah.....

 Here we are...that'll cheer me up....

Phwoar! Look at that toaster! Thats really nice... I'm feeling much better now...

MCR was really worth this kind of hangover thing I have now. They were excellent! Definatly different to all the other bands I have seen before. There was fire and Gerard came in on a hospital bed...but there was no zeplins, which was unhappy. I saw Ellen there, she was with her cousin I think, well, she was with a small child anyway. They were playing slapsies, but with out any goals, so basiclly there were just hitting each other. Ellen said she had a headache today in school, but I had a full scale riot in my brain, my ears were buzzing and I needed to got to the toilet every ten minutes. I have no idea why, I didn't eat or drink anything dodgy, I just had some coke-a-cola. Oh yeah, I also bought a pack of overpriced badges for a fiver. That was fun! Ellen and I swapped stories of drunks and junkies today. She had a drunk couple in front of her, swilling a bottle of red wine, and I had this druggy guy who was crying down his phone, shouting 'THEY'RE ON! THEY'RE FINALLY ON!". He also had swimming dance moves. 

Maybe I'm just a fucking saddo, but as soon as I saw Ellen, I wish I had gone with her instead. Mainly because Bethan was complaining about needing a wee, but...still. It was so much better though when she stopped complaining and went to the loo, but i still missed Ellen. Life is sad.

I think Mum is pissed with me. This might be because when I got in late last night I was behaving like a twat, and I begged her for a day off today. Now, she sent me to school, saying that I was only tierd and I didn't need to stay home for that, then I came home around 2nd lesson, because I was terrible. I think she thinks I am faking it or something. I did try though. I held out as long as I could in school, until I just thought 'Oh stuff it! Mum will get over it.' and let Mrs Shaw send me home. Mind you, I didn't even have to ask for a sick pass. In first lesson, Mr Evans (Mr I-wouldn't-want-my-man-to-smell-like-that!) asked me if I was ok, because according to Kimberly, I looked like I had a hangover. Then Mrs Shaw, saw me in second lesson. As soon as she noticed me, she offered me the pass, but I said no, because I wanted to see if I could cope all day. After I had run to the toilet again, I gave in. 
NOT MY FAULT!!!

I like colouring in. A lot. especially with felt tip.

Goodbye friends.

We went to a french/spanish open day today. It was very good and I learnt lots and lots...but I also had to endure Kate playing 'Chasing Cars' on her mobile on constent repeat. Then she went all sobby because the song made her think of this boy she fancies...which meant everyone went a little silent because we were thinking of ways to cheer her up (all of which failed miserably). My iPod had no battery left so I was stuck in that snow patrol induced misery world next to a moaning Kate. All wrist slashing worthy, I can tell you.
So on Saturday (maybe Sunday...I always get them two mixed up!). I am going with Bethan to MCR concert. I was kind of under the impression that it would be me, her and her cousin. Oh no, how wrong was I! Theres a huge crowd of us going....Seriously....masssive!!!! I think there's me, Bethan, her cousin, Bexy, Jade, Louisa 1, Louisa 2, her cousin's friends (maximum of 5), Jade's cousin, ect ect. Eep!
I have got back into the sims 2 now...BIG TIME!!! I've got the new seasons expansion pack and its increadible! Much better than even I expected! The snow effect is wonderful, it looks almost real and I was truely freaked out by the thunder .Poor little Alex K Sim (happy b'day by the way real alex....), he got burnt to death by a tree that caught fire after it was hit by lightning. Luckily, my sim was there and I told the grim reaper off and he's okay again now!!!!! WOOO!!!!!
I like music magazines that smell distinctive...
I cheating on the sims morally wrong???? 
Also, big dissapointment. The kaiser t-shirt I bought in the concert is too tight if I wear my super padded bra.....cry cry cry!  Normally, its fine, but I can't look super nice in it now. Waa....
Going to Greece in May. I am simply dreading wearing a swimming costume, I hate it. And I always look sweaty and pink in the photos. I wish we weren't going, or we were going somewhere cold instead (*cough*Sweden*cough*) 

ROXY MUSIC!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!(bryanferryscaresme)!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!(butilovehimanyway)!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

How do you use send space to send stuff and shizz?

I have found science-dude's band on myspace!!! God, I love the science department!  First Miss Carpenter knows one of the automatic, and now Gareth (who is this science person who wanders around wearing a white coat looking like he's ment to be there) is in a band! They're not that bad actually, it will need more listens though. They are called We Are Trees and the drummer, Gareth Barnes is the one that works in my school. I haven't actually heared him speak yet, just walk around looking important, with his hands in his pockets. One of my mates said he smiled at me, as I had my hands in my pockets too, and he probebly thought 'Oh there is another freak who likes keeping their hands in the warm'. 
So anyway, check them out. They don't appear to have been signed yet either (yeah, if they were signed, why the hell would he be working in a girls school?)
I am strangly excited about all this. I'm thinking of running up to him and going 'OMG! Your the drummer from We Are Trees! Can I have your autograph?' and I will just forget to tell him that I only know because Miss Carpenter told me. Nothing ever happens round here, so thats why I am excited. Also, they performed in the glee club in cardiff, which is where my cousin had his (short lived) comedy career. 

I am bored and going to hospital with my grandfather and mam. Just a check up. 
I might actually pick up my guitar today! SHOCK!!! HORROR!!! or maybe I'll just tinkle on my keyboard as usual.

Beep....beeep....neep....i can't think of anything else to say........
My mam got me jamie t's album. I am warming to him like a piece of hot toast. 
BYE!

I didn't post for a while. I was having 'so much fun' in school.
I gotta say Valentines in an only girls school is the most BORING ever! I didn't even realize that it was a special say until my mam gave me some pretty fairy lights! I got so bored that I actually told the lovely people at heidiseeker.com to write this really soppy thing with my order of funky gloves. Its really stupid and kinda sad considering I wrote it myself on the PC (in about 5 minutes) and got some poor sod to write it out for me. It goes like this

Dear Grace
I am sorry i can't say this to your face, I guess my self confindence ends there. I love you and I need you. Everytime I lok at you I think of how much I want you to be everything in my life
Be my girlfriend, be my wife. Be the mother of my children.
Be my valentine?
Alex xx
P.S Will you marry me?

The people actually covered my order in little stick on hearts with I love you written on them! I feel quite ashamed in case they actually thought it was real. 

Today was boring too. Me, Ellen, Kim and Alice were just sitting around talking about Jesus.  Oh yeah and I accidently flashed at Jess. we were getting changed after PE and I began to take of my bra, cause I forgot where I was. I am so stupid *bangs head on desk hard! *
I hate my Art teacher he's a little fuck. I prefer the student teacher because at least he talks to you nice. 
We also done this thing in school, a GCSE subject dry run. We had to pick some subjects that we were interested in, but not the final ones. Just some ideas. Because I picked triple science I can only do three other subjects. I picked Law, History and Religious Studies as my priorities and Drama for my reserve. 
Ah fuck it all. I am going to bed to eat Tobelorone!

(i was kind of hoping that Chive would text today, but I guess he's shacked up with new pair of scottish tights. Wanker :(  And i thought he was a nice boy...)

This is from an article about Kaisers in Word magzine....

'But its co-writing drummer, Nick Hodgson, releaser from backing-vocal exile, who provides the biggest surprise: Boxing Champ, a homoerotic piano lament with a touch of the Beautiful South about it. (We went to the youth club and we looked out of place/ I didn't know where to look so I looked at your face/ But you were a boxing champ and I was a weakling'

I can't wait!! The slash oppertunities are going to be ENDLESS!!! If my name isn't Oscar wilde...

i am over excitable I know.

So, I am kinda getting bored of the snow now. Its all mucking and melting now, making everywhere look dirty and wet. it was good while it lasted though...
I have mostly been writing in my fake diary as its too cold to go out. I love keeping a fake diary, you can just write whatever you want! At the moment I am a 23 year old medical student who is dating her tutor called Alan Pop (named after a virtual arty guy in Urbz:sims in the city for xbox. I know! I am a loser!) I have a brother in it called Lloyd who is an ex cocaine addict. 


Lord I'm bored. theres a rugby match on in the living room, so if I make a noise I get told off. I might actually be driven to do homework at this rate.

So yes...today!

The GOOD STUFF!
My ultra funky cats eyes glasses came today from Heidi Seeker! I look really cool (well, in my level of cool. To normal people I probebly look like a twat). It came with a gorgeous metallic case to keep them in with little squiggy cherries and ice creams on. I might wear them tomorrow to school with a big long scarf and a black coat, and I'll hang out with the drama students so I look like I belong SOMEWHERE
Micheal Newman is in the boys choir who my choir is mingling with. YESSS!!! He's hot and he wants to take over the world with me. He wears a rainbow scarf and waltzes around wearing his Captain Jack Harkness coat. I can't help but fancy him. Its just....YUM! He's my mates drum tutor though and he's 17, so I guess I haven't got a chance in hell. A girl can dream though...
erm...was there anymore good stuff?



No, I didn't think so.

The BAD STUFF!
Ellen wasn't in. boo!
Anna has told EVERYONE in my tutor group that I've met a 27 year old guy on the internet and I'm going to meet up with him. She is such a cow, I can't believe she spread rumours about me. What have I done? She fucking treats me like shit sometimes. Back when I was 12 she stole my diary and told everyone really personal things from it. She even threatened to put it on the computer and send it to all our boy mates. I was so upset, as I had confessed to fancying on of our boy mates in my diary. But I forgave her once she had apologised and gave it back. I'm so fucking stupid. I thought she would have grown up, but obviously not. She made me sound like a slapper and made people like Tara (not one of my big friends, but she is in my class) think its true and worry about me. 
Anna has a heart problem, so I feel guilty about being pissed with her now. I really want her to get better though. Her heart keeps getting this massive adreniline rush and starts to go real fast. I hope that its nothing too serious and I really want everything to be ok between us. She is a good friend when she isn't being a bitch. 

Isobel was on top form today though. She's funky!
It wasn't THAT bad a day though...it was ok.

I'm just a melodramatic whore I suppose. 
I nearly threw up this morning cause I had pineapple and tea for brekkie. BURGH!

So...yeah. Me and Ellen didn't talk much today. I really wanted to sit by her again (well, duh!), but you know. Alice and Kim were in the way again. I souldn't really feel sad, I mean, they have been friends for ages, way before I met any of them. I am just some new gal who just has a crush on her. 
yeah I do have a crush on her. First public mention of this I know, but it took me a lot longer to come to terms with it than I thought it would. There you go then...
It doesn't feel like this in slash is all I can tell you. 

So, anyway. I am officially not-as-skint-as-I-was-before. I have an extra fiver. Its going to 50pbadges.com (where I got my super cute Alex button picture at the top!squee!). 

I was tagged!!!
Once tagged by this entry, you list ten movies: your Five Favorites & your Five Guilty Pleasures. Then pick five of your friends and tag them. No tag-backs. This explanation should be included.

Faves
1.Donnie Darko
2.Pleasentville
3.Saun of The Dead
4.The Godfather
5.Scarface

Guilty Pleasures
1.Legally Blonde
2.Edward Scissorhands
3.Resident Evil (pretended not to like it because I am a big stupid snob. Sorry)
4.The Stepford Wives
5.Johnny English

Another thing that happened today. i was forced into singing infront of my whole house during house choir today. It was awful! they totally ignored my pleas of 'I'm an ALTO! YOU CAN'T PICK ON ME!!!!!!!' I was standing there looking like a nunce. Ellen came in and laughed at me, before smacking me on the arm and looking smug. Cow.



SHIT!!!!

I've got to learn my fucking welsh for wednesday!!!!

SHAG SHAGGEDY FUCK FUCK!!!!!!!

PHWOAR!!! I GOT TO MEET WITH MATT TODAY!!!! AREN'T I A LUCKY BITCH!!!!


Not really seeing as Matt is my insane gym instructor. who I fell over infront of when he asked me to drop my bum to the floor when I was doing lunges. then I laughed at him when he was doing the lunges because he looked so fucking SERIOUS!!! I think his head is too smal for his body. he's nice though, but I thought he was gay for ages (or rather wished). He's back from his honeymoon and he definatly got married to a she. 
he also has the annoying habit of measuring me all over. especially around the bust and arse. I have to stop myself blushing like an idiot.

My mum can't stop reading my slash. she loves it I think. she's even learned some of the terms such as PWP, schoolboy AU and angsty fic. She likes schoolboy. i don't mind but, I wish she'd get her own! I mean, I want to read about Alex and his little whores when I want to, not when she's finished with them. 

I also have learned how to upload pictures from the digital camera.

HOORAY!

Well, it was parent's evening today. I was feeling a little nervous, but ok. I shouldn't have worried. My teachers ever since Year One have never ever had anything bad to say about me. Its quite boring to be honest with you. I mean, this term, I though I'd been 'naughtier' than before, but apparently not. Even in maths (which i am shit at!) I was getting the best marks in the class. It sucks. I can't do this rebelious thing at all. And all my teachers actually like me and all of them want me to do a GCSE in their subjects! Even Mrs Rees-Peak, our evil bitchy music teacher, she gave me an A for our composing task and said she hoped that I at least considered higher level Music. I am, but if its against RE, which I really want to do long course in, then it hasn't got a chance. I do like music, I just think i can learn in different ways rather than sitting in class. Design and Technology is also going, I've decieded. Its a nice lesson and everything, and I enjoy it, but i have so much else to do and its not the thing I want to do most in the world. I think I am going to do triple science aswell, but the only lessons I am sure about is long course Re and Art. 
Today was kind of subdued. i guess some people were worried about the teachers meeting their parents. Anna has changed her tune about the GBS Club. She now wants to be part of it, and has designed t-shirts with me. They are really cool. What we are going to do is get nice, plain black t-shirts and put in quite big white letters on the front 'The GBS Club' and on the back rainbow letters spelling out 'coz some boys just wanna experiment'. We have also created rank patches that go on your shoulders. I am a gold patch as I am Kaiser Lexy (nickname).

I might try and write my first ever bit of Franz fiction. I've never had alex and the gang in a story before, its just been the Kaiser whores. Oh yeah, did you see the Kaisers in Q magazine? 4 stars outta 5 for their album, not bad pussycats! Ricky's looking older, but wiser too. Still love him. I also have Nicks nose, because I got these weird dents above the nostrils.

I love all of my friends at the moment, which is unusual. Usually, i'm pissed with at least one of them.

So I went back to school on Tuesday, had a mega fun time with my matey-bubs, then had a nasty cold for two days. I'm at home now, sniffling and writing in my fake diary. For some reason, I feel really weird about keeping a normal diary, but I love, love LOVE writing in my fake one. It makes the days go quicker and makes me feel less depressed. I am depressed. I suck. 
We managed to get Kaiser tickets which I am really pleased about. Me, kate, isobel and jess were talking about saving up our own money to buy tickets and go with each other, but when I came home from school and found there was hardly any tickets left, it was every woman for herself. I want the others to come, seriously I do, but I don't think I'm prepared to give up my spot in the concert just to show companionship. Anyway, if they do manage to get tickets from somewhere, then it would be super cool if they could be with me and my mum (yes my mum is into Kaisers. She thinks Nick seems like a nice young boy)
i have been mostly downloading music today. At the moment I have a LOT of The Shins and Sufjan Stevens, plus Prince, the Beastie Boys and Harry and the Potters (I have nothing better to do). i am very bored....
My mother and I have been playing the Godfather game on Playstation all over the Christmas break. It's kind of weird, bonding over intense violence. Mum can't drive the cars to save her life. I am just a supersonic killing machine with a garote wire and a habit of killing the wrong people (members of the public, policemen, mobsters on my side ect.)

I was going to say something else, but i can't remember. it was very funny and you would have liked it. Oh well...
the title of the song I am listening to is too long for the stupid boxy thing, so I will put it here instead

music: Sufjan Stevens - they are night zombies!! they are neighbours!! they are back from the dead!! AHHHH!!!

Capiche?

I dunno what time it is. I have a clok at the bottome of the screen but i can't be arsed to work out the time from a 24 hour clock. I have had a babyshame and a bottle of becks and its gone to my head.I am a lightweight. I am trying to buy Franz Ferdinand videos off iTunes, but iTunes wont give me it. I think that a lot of peeps has iPod for Christmas and they want to make it work. I will do it tommorrow.
I am very please . I am also tired.
Merry Christmas....

This si a picture of Rufus Wainwright in a hat. I drew it myself on paint (well, the hat and the present bit).

Goodbye.

Well, I'm back. Good to see that everyone's missed me (not). I'm really trying not to let it get to be (no one should be lonely during Christmas!) but you know how it is. I didn't even get any e-mails of my school mates. They must really hate me. Or just listen to me when I tell them my internet is off for ages. Merry Christmas *blub* .
So, we got messed aroung by BT (BIG TIME!!!) We don't even get our broadband from them, but we still managed to spend more time on the phone getting chewed up arse shit from then than we did actually getting the internet from Tiscali (who were actually very efficiant). We had to ring up BT four times to ask them to clear out line of TAGs (don't ask me what they are...) and the last time they said they had actually done it the day before we last phoned. Plus, when we were trying to get some infomation out of them, the staff were rude and acted as though we were just stupid costumers who could be treated like scum! I can't help but think that in places like Sweden, where the consumer services are supposed to be second to none, they must get treated better than this. Or is this what the world considers polite, and am I just the stupid, insane one?
During my time away from the internet I have bought the new Beatles album, fallen down stairs, lost my RE book, sang in the senior choir for the first time on stage, said good bye to my favourite teacher and...did a lot of other things as well. I also have the coolest bookcase in the world! It has these things that you can remove from the door, decorate however you want, then slip it back in! Mine is beautiful, it has a zebra flavoured background with Alex Kapranos, seahorses and other great things like a Smiths spewing iPod! Mieow!
I am going now. Bye
Grace

...has nothing at all to do with me. 

Tommorow my internet is being switched off for a good while when we move to the new house fully. God knows when it will be put back on. I am very sad about this, as I love my internet, but at least I can still play the Sims 2 (I have got back into it now, NICK HAD PUPPIES!!). I will try and continue to update my journal by using the libary PCs/ using school PCs (not really allowed but you know)/ pinching my friends computers. This is just a notice so you know that if I don't reply promptly, its because of this.

Well, when we were clearing out the attic, I found tonnes and tonnes of my mother's old LPs. There was some seriouslty fantastic stuff up there too, and being the lovely person that she is, she let me keep the two vintage Pixies ones. YAY! HOORAY! They are deffinatly NOT going on Ebay ( I wish the same could be said about my fathers music collection...)

THE KAISERS ARE INTERVIEWING DOCTOR WHO IN THE NME YEAR BOOK!!! That is the best news of this fortnight. lol

Ciao for now, my chums and chumettes. I don't know when you will hear from me again, but you will. Try not to cry too much.

Grace

I don't really know whether I am being helpful or just annoying, but I was cleaning out my room and I came across these kind of old Franz Ferdinand pictures, which I don't think I have seen anywhere online. They were in the 1st of October issue in 2005. I thought that I should put them up here just incase someone would like them.
I'm sorry if you've seen them all before!



















Feel free to muck around with them as much as you like!

I spent today cleaning our new house and now, my hands are dry from all that CILLIT BANG! Our new house is ace, I have a Thomas the Tank Engine room! WOOP WOOP! It ain't going to stay like that though. I am thinking of a white room with laminate floor and two of the facing walls will be painted a black board paint so you can doodle on it and then the ceiling will be black with white/silver stars. Its either that or a black and red Franz-style bedroom, but I think that would be too difficult for my parents. Oh well...
I got a present of the new Sims 2 expansion pack. I think its called Pets and its supposed to be good. Its been a while since I was heavily into sims, I used to be addicted to it. I'm thinking of getting back into it.

I am excited about going to see My Chemical Romance with Bethan. I know its early next year and everything, but I can feel the excitement rising in my stomache.  Come Christmas, I will be hyper!

Another thing to look forward to is that in 6 weeks i will be having blonde slashes put in my hair. It SHOULD look nice, but if done in a bad way, could look chavvy. If that happens, I am just going to shave my hair off.

 

Bye bye!

I am miserable because my tripods died in the night ( it was too cold for them and now only one is left, poor little thing), Trisha wasn't as good as it was before and I look wonderful for once, but I have no where to go. 

I also have melted chocolate on my skinny jeans that I have never noticed before.

Anyway, here is the answer for the iPod game thing. I gotta say I thought people would get more of them than that, but I do admit I maybe was a bit mean with the tracks I chose to skip (I skipped over the Libertines as I thought too many people would get it)

1) On your current playlist, hit shuffle and pick the first twenty-five songs on the list (no matter how cheesy or embarrassing).
2) Write down a line of the song. Try to avoid putting the song title in the line.
3) Have your friends comment and see if they know the songs. (NO CHEATING!) <-Please don't use a net search. That's no fun!
4) When someone guesses correctly, strike out the line and list the correct name of the song next to it.
5) If someone guesses the artist and not the song, list the correct artist but not the song (Do not strike out.).
6) If someone guesses the song and not the artist, list the song title but not the artist (Do not strike out).
7) You must state if your lyric is a cover version. If it's the original, you don't have to say. If you aren't sure, it doesn't matter

Once upon a time there was a lovely young man named Ricky Wilson who lived all on his own in Happy Land, where everyone turned their condoms inside out to save money. He was quite short when one thinks about it, and he was also ginger which meant that all the other men in Happy Land teased him because they were shallow bitches who do up their skinny jeans to tight.
One day Ricky went on a long walk into the deep dark woods and suddenly, he came across a tall, handsome young man doing something to a tree.
"Hello tall, dark stranger." Said Ricky, "What do you happen to be doing?"
"I am trying to milk this tree so I can buy a house for me and my 322000 kids to live in," Said the man "Money is very tight in our house. They all want iPods for Christmas too." 
Ricky felt very sorry for the man, as he knew that children were a pain. He saw one in the zoo once, it was dead scary!  
"Whats your name young man, who seems so very frisky?" 
Suddenly, the wood turned bright and sunny and the young man gave off a tremenous glow, almost like an angel of the lord. The man seemed to grow in height, until he was almost as tall as the mighty oak, before booming in a great loud voice, "MY NAME IS RYAN JARMAN, KEEPER OF THE GIANT PEA!!!" 
"That's nice, I'm Ricky and I work in Tescos."

It was then Ricky noticed a hole in the trunk of the tree. It seemed to him to be shapedas a can of lager, but maybe that was because he was pissed. Or high. Or maybe both. Anyway, it was a magical rotating lager shaped hole in the tree so naturally Ricky wanted to put his hand in it.
Slowly he extended his hand, feeling the temperature increase with every centimetre. He was so close, then Ryan slapped his hand playfully.
"You have to treat me good before I let you touch my hole, Ricky Wilson."
Ricky gasped in shock.
"How did you know my name?"
"You told it to me a minute ago, you dickhead."
Ricky then suduced Ryan. I can't really explain how he did it. All I know is that he used a long pointy stick, some silly string and tampax compact. 
"Are you going to touch my hole now?" said Ryan, the tampon string hanging out his mouth like a mouse's tail.
"You better believe it, baby."
And Ricky touched the hole...

The whole world collapsed, and suddenly Ricky found himself falling through a great abyss. He tried to grab onto something, but all he could find was swivel chairs which is no help to anyone while stuck in a Super Massive Black Hole.
Finally, after what seemed like an eternity, he landed on something very hard and shiny. He tried to move, but everytime he did so, a weird twangy noise played out really loudly.
"Dom! DOM! Thier's a strange man lieing on my guitar!"
Ricky knew then that he was in trouble. He was in the presence of someone who did not know the correct gramma. Could it get any worse? He was about to find out....
A great, raven haired figure stood before him. The figure was clad in a red military coat that Ricky recognized from the pages of vogue. The man before him was also wearing a name tag, with the letters : Hi! My name is MATT BELLAMY and I'm here to help! written on it.
"Who are you?" Ricky croaked because he couldn't be arsed to get his reading glasses out.
"I AM MATT BELLAMY< KEEPER OF THE GIANT PEA!"
"But I thought Ryan Jarman was the keeper of the giant pea?"
'NO, HE'S JUST THE KEEPER OF THE KEEPER OF THE GIANT PEA"
"Oh ...right." said Ricky and he promptly fainted












Ricky came to in a small dungeon room with only one window. It was horribly dark in there, and the air seemed heavy and dead. It kinda reminded him of his local though, so he felt quite safe.
"SO MR WILSON!" came a very loud, piercing voice from the corner of the room. "YOU HAVE DECIEDED TO AWAKE!"
Ricky looked around to see MATT BELLAMY sitting on a chair, stroking what appeared to be a cat, but upon closer inspection, revealed itself to be nothing more than a large, fluffy muffin.
"Erm...whats going on MATT BELLAMY?" said Ricky, the feeling of comfort fading fast.
"CAN YOU NOT WORK IT OUT, YOU LITTLE ART SCHOOL TWAT! YOU HAVE BEEN KIDNAPPED AND HELD FOR RANSOM UNTIL EITHER SOMEONE PAYS UP OR YOU HAVE HOT GAY SEX WITH ME, WHICH EVER COMES SOONER! SUCK ON THAT BIG BOY!" MATT BELLAMY cackled evily.
"But why me? What have I done to deserve this?"
"WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE YOU STEPPED ON A SNAIL, AM I CORRECT?"
"Er, yes..."
"THAT SNAIL WAS CALLED TERRANCE AND HE WAS MY BESTEST FRIEND."
         Ricky would have then felt sorry for MATT BELLAMY, if he hadn't then got out a pair of fluffy handcuffs and strapped Ricky to the bed. 
Ricky spent 4 weeks in MATT BELLAMY's dungeon. All he could do was stare at the ceiling or compose small whistleing songs about cars with breasts. His only contact was with a man named Alex Kapranos, who was MATT BELLAMY's sex slave. Alex seemed only able to communicate with strange phrases such as 'Your are a beautiful dance whore' or ' Well, do you, do ya, do ya wanna?'. One day, Ricky had enough.
"Oi! Alex!" 
"Find me and follow me, through corridors refactories?"
"Alex, would you like to escape from this crazy dungeon of sex and lies and guitars and sex and space and sex and...."
"Lucky, lucky, you're so lucky!"
Ricky took this as a Yes, so he wriggled out of his bondage, and they started their amazing escape.
They dug, they swam, they ran away from the castle of MATT BELLAMY until they entered entered a dark spooky cave. It was then suddenly, Alex spoke
"HOORAY!!!! I no longer have to speak in song lyrics!"
Ricky looked at him strangely.
Alex continued, "For years I have been stuck in the castle, cursed with only being able to speak in saucy rock lyrics. I was told that one day a funny ginger bloke with dodgy skin will come and rescue me, and now it has come true! Now I can fufill my dream of becoming a stripper! Thank you!"
Alex then kissed Ricky.
"Oh yeah, by the way. Find out about the giant pea..." said Alex, before skipping off into the darkness, leaving Ricky with those words running around his ginger little brain.

Find out about the giant pea... What did that mean anyway? Ricky thought he knew all he needed to know about the giant pea. It was a big pea! What was there left to discover about it? Although, saying that, it must be a pretty darn special vegtable to have so much mystery surrounding it...
Ricky was so busy pondering the existance of the giant pea, he didn't notice how far he had got into the cave. It was pitch black when he realised. He felt quite scared then.
Suddenly he saw a light right next to him and a hand on his shoulder.
"WHO THE FUCK IS THAT!!!!" Ricky screamed petrified, trying to run for it, but the hand holding him where he was.
"Calm down you dunce! Your the one in MY cave so really I should be asking you that question..." 
The light was turned up to reaveal the face of a rather lovely looking young man. The light bounced of his sparkly blonde hair and his deep chocoltae eyes.
"Anyway, my name is Beck and I live in this cave."
'He must be a right knob if he lives in a cave.' thought Ricky 'Oh well, maybe he can help me out.'
But before Ricky could ask him, he was shoved down to his knees and something long, hard, smooth and damp was shoved in his mouth. 
"Sit down and eat this banana, sorry its a bit wet. I think it rained on it once.' said Beck , before starting to make tea.
Ricky was grateful for the banana, as he was getting rather peckish, so he munched it all up. As Beck turned up the light even more, Ricky caught sight of a whole mound of fruit. Melons, grapes, lemons, even kiwis were there.
"Don't suppose you have any apples, do you Beck?"
"Why the fuck would I have apples in a frgging CAVE, for fucks sake! You must be a right cock  to think I'd have an apple in this fucking CAVE!"
Ricky thought that he didn't need to be so rude, but he didn't like to say so because Beck had a really long pointy stick in his trouser pocket which he was rather scared of.
Ricky then started to cry. He had just realised that he had been scared shitless for a long time and, OH MY GOD! He couldn't believe it! He had never ever been so far away from home!
Beck sighed, rolling his eyes slightly, "Whats wrong now? You come in here! Eat my lovely fruit, then you get all emo on my ass!"
"I wanna go home!" Ricky sobbed "I wanna be in my bed and watch CSI and wank, and just be a normal man, instead of going on this crazy adventure! I had a life in Happy Land!"
"Not much of one, is what I've heard. News travels quickly around here."
Beck got a piece of paper out of his pocket, unfolding it and holding to up for Ricky to read. It said RICKY WILSON IS A TWAT AND HAS NO FRIENDS. This made Ricky cry even more.
Beck may have felt a little sorry for our hero then. He was a ginger nut after all. 
"Come on then. I'll get you outta here."
He grabbed Ricky by the hand.
"Now hold on tightly or you'll get lost!"
And he began to lead him out of the cave.

It didn't take that long to get to the cave enterence . It was a still night and Ricky could hear the crickets sing in the near by woods.
"Thank you" he began before turning around to see Beck hiding in a corner. 
He seemed in pain and was screaming very loudly
"RUN!" he howled, "RUN AS FAST AS YOUR GINGER LEGS WILL CARRY YOU!!"
"Why, whats up?" said ricky, rushing over to help, because in girl guides he was told never to leave a friend in danger.
Beck seemed a lot different from before. He was now wearing a funk y hat and in his hands he had two turntables and a microphone. He turned to face Ricky,
"I should have told you sooner!"
"Told me what?"
"I AM A WERE-BECK! BY DAY, I AM JUST A HARMLESS BLOKE, BUT BY THE LIGHT OF THE MOON...I BECOME THE VICIOUS, FUNK-A-DELIC KING OF HIP MUSIC!!"
Ricky started to run then, because in girl guides he was told to fuck off when something big and scary was comeing.

What do you think these boys are doing, eh?

Mostly everyone in my class (including moi) think they're 'being extra friendly' but my teacher insists that they are fighting. 
"Girls, why would they be in a Welsh book if they were kissing?" she said
Well why would they be fighting next to the sentence Ces I amser da gyda fy ffrindiau yn gwneud dim byd yn arbennig (roughly translated : I had a great time with friends doing NOTHING IN PARTICULAR) Welsh is now my favourite subject, after science that is. Gay boy science.
                 I feel blah. 
It was then Ricky noticed a hole in the trunk of the tree. It seemed to him to be shaped as a can of lager, but maybe that was because he was pissed. Or high. Or maybe both. Anyway, it was a magical rotating lager shaped hole in the tree so naturally Ricky wanted to put his hand in it.
       Slowly he extended his hand, feeling the temperature increase with every centimetre. He was so close, then Ryan slapped his hand playfully.
"You have to treat me good before I let you touch my hole, Ricky Wilson."
Ricky gasped in shock.
"How did you know my name?"
"You told it to me a minute ago, you dickhead."
Ricky then suduced Ryan. I can't really explain how he did it. All I know is that he used a long pointy stick, some silly string and tampax compact. 
"Are you going to touch my hole now?" said Ryan, the tampon string hanging out his mouth like a mouse's tail.
"You better believe it, baby."
And Ricky touched the hole...

The whole world collapsed, and suddenly Ricky found himself falling through a great abyss. He tried to grab onto something, but all he could find was swivel chairs which is no help to anyone while stuck in a Super Massive Black Hole.
         Finally, after what seemed like an  Eternity, he landed on something very hard and shiny. He tried to move, but everytime he did so, a weird twangy noise played out really loudly.
"Dom! DOM! Thier's a strange man lieing on my guitar!"
Ricky knew then that he was in trouble. He was in the presence of someone who did not know the correct gramma. Could it get any worse? He was about to find out....
A great, raven haired figure stood before him. The figure was clad in a red military coat that Ricky recognized from the pages of vogue. The man before him was also wearing a name tag, with the letters : Hi! My name is MATT BELLAMY and I'm here to help! written on it.
"Who are you?" Ricky croaked because he couldn't be arsed to get his reading glasses out.
"I AM MATT BELLAMY< KEEPER OF THE GIANT PEA!"
"But I thought Ryan Jarman was the keeper of the giant pea?"
'NO, HE'S JUST THE KEEPER OF THE KEEPER OF THE GIANT PEA"
"Oh ...right." said Ricky and he promptly fainted.

To be continued...

Erm, here's a lovely story that I'm just going to make up off the top of my head. 

Ricky Wilson and The Giant Pea 

Once upon a time there was a lovely young man named Ricky Wilson who lived all on his own in Happy Land, where everyone turned their condoms inside out to save money. He was quite short when one thinks about it, and he was also ginger which meant that all the other men in Happy Land teased him because they were shallow bitches who do up their skinny jeans to tight. 
     One day Ricky went on a long walk into the deep dark woods and suddenly, he came across a tall, handsome young man doing something to a tree. 
"Hello tall, dark stranger." Said Ricky, "What do you happen to be doing?" 
"I am trying to milk this tree so I can buy a house for me and my 322000 kids to live in," Said the man "Money is very tight in our house. They all want iPods for Christmas too." 
       Ricky felt very sorry for the man, as he knew that children were a pain. He saw one in the zoo once, it was dead scary!  
"Whats your name young man, who seems so very frisky?" 
Suddenly, the wood turned bright and sunny and the young man gave off a tremenous glow, almost like an angel of the lord. The man seemed to grow in height, until he was almost as tall as the mighty oak, before booming in a great loud voice, "MY NAME IS RYAN JARMAN, KEEPER OF THE GIANT PEA!!!" 
"Thats nice, I'm Ricky and I work in Tescos."

people you actually know and go with your first instinct.

Scroll down one line at a time...and don't read ahead or you'll ruin it!

1. First, write the numbers 1 through 11 in a column.














2. Then, beside numbers 1 and 2, write down any two numbers you want.










3. Beside the 3 and 7, write down the names of members of the opposite sex.
















NO LOOKING AHEAD...OR IT WON"T TURN OUT RIGHT!




4. Write anyone's name (like friends or family....) in the 4th, 5th,and 6th
spots.












5. Write down four song titles in 8,9,10, and 11.












GO WITH YOUR INSTINCT PEOPLE!!!!






6. Finally, make a wish.
















And now the key for the game.....









1. You must tell (the number in space 2) people about this game.
















2. The person in space 3 is the one that you love.


















3. The person in 7 is one you like but can't work out.

















4. You care most about the person you put in 4



















5. The person you name in number 5 is the one who knows you very well.



















6. The person you name in 6 is your lucky star.





















7. The song in 8 is the song that matches with the person in number 3.















8. The title in 9 is the song for the person in 7.

















9. The tenth space is the song that tells you most about YOUR mind.

















10. and 11 is the song telling you how you feel about life
